x4freetext: Experiment conducted at the Lawrence
Berkeley Laboratory`s (LBL) Bevalac accelerator.
Experimental arrangement consisted of array of 4
paralel plate ionization chambers, two Cherenkov
counters nd multiwire proportional chambers. Sample
was located between first and second ionization
chamber.
Each ionization chamber had four active volumes
filled with P10 gas and 28.06 cm, separated with mylar
electrodes with thickness of 0.000635 cm.
Cherenkov counters had two Pilot 425 radiators,
each 0.569 cm thick. Radiator was doped with wave
shifter to reemit light isotropically. Photomultipliers
were placed in such manner as to maximize  difuse
reflection of collected light.
multiwire proportional counter was mounted
directly in front of the Cherenkov counters and were
filled with Ar+5%CO2 gas.
Corrections for target-out and thick target were made
Compiled by S.H.
Sample thicknesses were chosen so, that the incident
beam energy loss in the target was 100 MeV. Particle
energy at the mid-target is given as incident energy
